%N A138044 Primes formed from the concatenation of primitive Pythagorean triples.
%H A138044 Carlo Corti, <a href="/A138044/b138044.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..7470</a>
%H A138044 Carlo Corti, <a href="/A138044/a138044.txt">Table of n, a(n), p1, p2, p3, e1, e2 for n=1..7470</a>
%H A138044 Carlo Corti, <a href="https://github.com/carcorti/A138044">A138044: Complete 64-bit computational extension of OEIS sequence A138044</a>
%F A138044 c(e1,e2) = concat(min(e1^2-e2^2,2*e1*e2), max(e1^2-e2^2,2*e1*e2), e1^2+e2^2), where e1 > e2 >= 1, gcd(e1,e2)=1, and e1-e2 is odd; a(n) runs through the prime values of c(e1,e2). - _Carlo Corti_, May 29 2026
%e A138044 Entries 7999601249 and 8536123613, for instance, are primes obtained respectively from the primitive Pythagorean triples (799,960,1249) and (85,3612,3613).
